WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.170 --> 00:00:00.930
Why I fight,

1
00:00:01.129 --> 00:00:01.370
run,

2
00:00:01.490 --> 00:00:02.509
or shut down

3
00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:05.010
understanding survival responses.

4
00:00:05.769 --> 00:00:06.429
Sometimes

5
00:00:06.969 --> 00:00:09.189
I don't react the way you expect me to.

6
00:00:09.609 --> 00:00:11.270
You might ask me something simple

7
00:00:11.409 --> 00:00:12.510
and I snap back

8
00:00:12.689 --> 00:00:13.850
or I walk away,

9
00:00:14.140 --> 00:00:16.600
or I just go quiet and stop responding.

10
00:00:17.010 --> 00:00:17.829
From the outside

11
00:00:18.170 --> 00:00:19.930
it can look like I'm being difficult

12
00:00:20.180 --> 00:00:21.379
or ignoring you

13
00:00:21.649 --> 00:00:23.370
or choosing not to engage,

14
00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:24.879
but that's not what's happening.

15
00:00:25.129 --> 00:00:26.010
What you're seeing.

16
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:28.280
Is my body trying to protect me?

17
00:00:28.559 --> 00:00:32.259
There are times when something inside me suddenly feels unsafe.

18
00:00:32.598 --> 00:00:34.220
It might be something small,

19
00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:35.540
a tone of voice,

20
00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:36.319
a look,

21
00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:38.419
a situation that feels familiar.

22
00:00:38.599 --> 00:00:39.919
You might not notice it,

23
00:00:40.119 --> 00:00:40.959
but I do.

24
00:00:41.119 --> 00:00:43.470
And before I've had time to think about it,

25
00:00:43.759 --> 00:00:45.040
my body reacts.

26
00:00:45.229 --> 00:00:47.490
That's when I go into what people call fight,

27
00:00:47.950 --> 00:00:48.389
flight,

28
00:00:48.630 --> 00:00:49.409
or freeze.

29
00:00:49.630 --> 00:00:50.590
If I go into fight,

30
00:00:50.740 --> 00:00:51.540
you'll see anger.

31
00:00:51.669 --> 00:00:52.310
I might shout,

32
00:00:52.430 --> 00:00:52.759
swear,

33
00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:53.540
push boundaries,

34
00:00:53.549 --> 00:00:54.389
or challenge you.

35
00:00:54.590 --> 00:00:56.099
It can look like I'm being aggressive,

36
00:00:56.270 --> 00:00:57.650
like I'm trying to take control,

37
00:00:57.990 --> 00:00:59.229
but what's really happening

38
00:00:59.509 --> 00:01:02.630
is I feel under threat and my body is trying to defend me.

39
00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:03.950
If I go into flight.

40
00:01:04.328 --> 00:01:05.369
I might leave the room,

41
00:01:05.549 --> 00:01:06.509
refuse to engage,

42
00:01:06.689 --> 00:01:07.869
or avoid you completely.

43
00:01:08.009 --> 00:01:09.638
It might look like I don't care,

44
00:01:09.929 --> 00:01:12.039
like I'm walking away from responsibility,

45
00:01:12.289 --> 00:01:12.958
but I'm not.

46
00:01:13.128 --> 00:01:15.759
I'm trying to get away from something that feels too much,

47
00:01:16.049 --> 00:01:17.088
and then there's freeze.

48
00:01:17.249 --> 00:01:18.289
That's when I shut down.

49
00:01:18.369 --> 00:01:19.049
I go quiet.

50
00:01:19.168 --> 00:01:20.149
I stop talking.

51
00:01:20.488 --> 00:01:21.899
Sometimes I don't respond at all.

52
00:01:22.098 --> 00:01:23.738
It might look like I'm being rude

53
00:01:23.888 --> 00:01:25.268
or ignoring you on purpose,

54
00:01:25.609 --> 00:01:26.308
but inside.

55
00:01:26.949 --> 00:01:28.099
I'm overwhelmed.

56
00:01:28.309 --> 00:01:30.739
It's like everything just stops in those moments.

57
00:01:30.830 --> 00:01:32.059
I'm not thinking clearly.

58
00:01:32.309 --> 00:01:34.300
The part of my brain that helps me understand,

59
00:01:34.750 --> 00:01:34.989
process,

60
00:01:35.029 --> 00:01:35.889
and respond,

61
00:01:36.190 --> 00:01:37.370
it's not fully there.

62
00:01:37.720 --> 00:01:39.220
My body has taken over,

63
00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:40.699
and once that happens,

64
00:01:40.919 --> 00:01:43.739
I can't just switch it off because someone tells me to calm down.

65
00:01:44.230 --> 00:01:45.430
That's not how it works.

66
00:01:45.639 --> 00:01:47.790
This is why your response matters so much,

67
00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:49.400
because when I'm in that state,

68
00:01:49.559 --> 00:01:50.980
I'm not choosing behavior.

69
00:01:51.129 --> 00:01:54.000
I'm reacting to how safe or unsafe I feel.

70
00:01:54.190 --> 00:01:55.599
If voices get louder,

71
00:01:55.879 --> 00:01:56.879
if I feel cornered,

72
00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:58.699
if things become unpredictable,

73
00:01:58.959 --> 00:02:01.080
my brain reads that as more danger,

74
00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:02.519
and everything escalates.

75
00:02:02.739 --> 00:02:04.040
But when you stay calm,

76
00:02:04.199 --> 00:02:05.239
even when I'm not.

77
00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:07.279
When your voice stays steady,

78
00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:09.720
when you give me space instead of closing in,

79
00:02:10.008 --> 00:02:11.880
when you don't take it personally,

80
00:02:12.289 --> 00:02:13.389
something changes.

81
00:02:13.690 --> 00:02:15.830
My body starts to feel less under threat.

82
00:02:15.929 --> 00:02:17.470
It doesn't happen instantly,

83
00:02:17.690 --> 00:02:18.720
but it starts.

84
00:02:18.970 --> 00:02:20.729
That's what helps me come out of it.

85
00:02:21.050 --> 00:02:22.429
That's what helps me regulate

86
00:02:23.039 --> 00:02:23.610
over time.

87
00:02:23.729 --> 00:02:26.009
That's how I learn a different way of responding.

88
00:02:26.649 --> 00:02:27.690
Not through punishment,

89
00:02:27.860 --> 00:02:28.800
not through control,

90
00:02:29.220 --> 00:02:31.339
but through feeling safe enough to think again.

91
00:02:31.419 --> 00:02:33.679
I'm not expecting you to get it right every time,

92
00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:34.830
but what I need

93
00:02:34.979 --> 00:02:36.279
is consistency.

94
00:02:36.660 --> 00:02:38.830
I need to know what to expect from you.

95
00:02:38.979 --> 00:02:40.929
I need to know that even when I react,

96
00:02:41.139 --> 00:02:43.720
you're not going to react in a way that makes things worse,

97
00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:46.039
because behind my behavior

98
00:02:46.380 --> 00:02:48.500
is a system that's learned to survive.

99
00:02:48.779 --> 00:02:49.990
And when you understand that you,

100
00:02:50.139 --> 00:02:51.259
you don't just see behavior,

101
00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:52.720
you see what's driving it,

102
00:02:52.979 --> 00:02:54.220
and that changes everything.